          "tz": 540
        },
        "subject": "LU-1432 ptlrpc: LBUG in lprocfs_free_client_stats()",
        "message": "LU-1432 ptlrpc: LBUG in lprocfs_free_client_stats()\n\nWhen target_handle_connect() does reconnection with an existing export\nobject obtained from lustre_hash_lookup(), the refcount of the export\nobject may reach zero while still being used there.\nThis case ends up in two phenomena, the one is causing OS-panic when\nthe export object has already been released, the other is the LBUG in\nlprocfs_free_client_stats() when the export object has still been\nlisted in obd_zombie_exports and not released yet.\n\nThis patch adjusts the refcount of export in target_handle_connect()\nproperly in order not to cause the above phenomena and serialize\nclass_cleanup() and target_handle_connect() in order to remove the\nrace-condition of obd_nid_hash\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nSigned-off-by: Lai Siyao <laisiyao@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ibc3caf7e1426a3a99f059df0faabd7bb7314bbe8\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
